>I'd like to learn more about digital encryption, but I really don't know where
>to start.  While the people who discuss digital encryption (DES,DVP,etc.) are
>obviously quite knowledgeable (from sci.crypt), I can't follow the
>conversation with only basic understanding of the subject.  What books,
>peroidicals, etc, could I access to get a start?

>Brad Steinman
>University of Toledo Computer Services
>cscon0151@uoft02.utoledo.edu

Try the following...

Denning, D. Cryptography and Data Security
Addison-Wesley, 1982

Patterson, W.  Mathematical Cryptology
Rowman & Littlefield, 1987

Salomaa, A. Public-key Cryptography
Berlin, Germany: Springer-Verlag, 1990

Have fun! ;-)


